benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: Valid Request: Multiple scenarios validate successful resume paths (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04).
Non-Existing Resource: TC05 covers 404 when bundle not found.
Authorization: TC07 (missing header) and TC10 (invalid/unauthorized token) cover auth handling.
Validation: TC06 (invalid bundleId), TC20 (requestedDate in past), TC19 (invalid pluginProperty format) test input validation.
State machine / Concurrency: TC08 (not paused), TC09 (cancelled), TC21 (concurrent requests) cover state transitions and race conditions.
Server Error Handling: TC14 (system error due to dependency) and TC15 (retry after transient failure) cover error scenarios and resilience.
Header/Parameter Variants: TC04 (all optional headers), TC12 (max length headers), TC18 (partial input), TC25 (integration with degraded service) test variations.
Security: TC16 (SQL injection in pluginProperty) and TC17 (XSS in X-Killbill-Comment) address security concerns.
Regression and Backward Compatibility: TC23 (edge case regression) and TC24 (legacy headers) ensure stability across changes.
Performance: TC22 (load/throughput) and TC25 (integration latency) address performance considerations.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for rate limiting or throttling under bursty traffic.
Caching Behavior: No tests verifying HTTP caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or related caching behavior.
Explicit Response Content: Several success paths rely on 204 without body; no tests asserting exact response bodies beyond status and basic messages, which may be desired for full validation.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under bursts or high concurrency.
Introduce tests around HTTP caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) to verify caching behavior.
Enhance some 204 responses with explicit payload verification where applicable, or document that empty bodies are expected to ensure clarity.
